Assignment <3>
Organization
Explanation of the created structure, or of the chosen overall solution:

To solve this assignment, I used the code from the samples (epoll_echo_server.c and http_reply_once.c), 
plus the exercise from the old OS lab about asynchronous operations (kaio.c). Apart from that, I had 
to implement sending the header and the files. I also implemented non-blocking reading and writing.
I believe I implemented a fairly good algorithm, but I do not know whether a more efficient algorithm 
exists. I think the hardest part was the non-blocking sockets, because a connection had to remember 
many variables and states when it finished reading/writing.

Implementation

Reading the request is similar to the examples, except that it is non-blocking, because I call the 
recv()/send() functions until I have read everything. If I have not finished reading, the connection 
still has bytes to send, but it also has to let other connections run their operations.

For static files, I called the sendfile function until I had sent all the bits, and for dynamic files
I used the aio functions for reading. For writing, I used the send function together with all the 
buffers into which data had been read from the file.
